quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  7,171,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We raised the mountain over them as if it were a cloud and they thought it would fall on them.¬†ňĻWe said,ňļ ‚ÄúHold firmly to that ňĻScriptureňļ which¬†We have given you and observe its teachings so perhaps you will become mindful ňĻof Allahňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  7,172,"And ňĻrememberňļ when your Lord brought forth from the loins of the children of Adam their descendants and had them testify regarding themselves. ňĻAllah asked,ňļ ‚ÄúAm I not your Lord?‚ÄĚ They replied, ‚ÄúYes, You are! We testify.‚ÄĚ ňĻHe cautioned,ňļ ‚ÄúNow you have no right to say on Judgment Day, ‚ÄėWe were not aware of this.‚Äô"
  7,173,"Nor say, ‚ÄėIt was our forefathers who had associated others ňĻwith Allah in worshipňļ and we, as their descendants, followed in their footsteps. Will you then destroy us for the falsehood they invented?‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  7,174,"This is how We make our signs clear, so perhaps they will return ňĻto the Right Pathňļ"
  7,175,"And relate to them ňĻO Prophetňļ the story of the one to whom We gave Our signs, but he abandoned them, so Satan took hold of him, and he became a deviant"
  7,176,"If We had willed, We would have elevated him with Our signs, but he clung to this life‚ÄĒfollowing his evil desires. His example is that of a dog: if you chase it away, it pants, and if you leave it, it ňĻstillňļ pants. This is the example of the people who deny Our signs.¬†So narrate ňĻto themňļ stories ňĻof the pastňļ, so perhaps they will reflect"
  7,177,What an evil example of those who denied Our signs! They ňĻonlyňļ wronged their own souls
  7,178,"Whoever Allah guides is truly guided. And whoever He leaves to stray, they are the ňĻtrueňļ losers"